    public enum UniScriptBuiltIn

implements BuiltInInterface
    This Enum defines a set of constants, each of which specifies a Unicode "script" of characters to be matched (see below). Each of these Enum constants can be used to instantiate a BuiltInCharClass that matches any of the characters in the corresponding Unicode script. For example, 

          Pattern Arabic = new BuiltInCharClass(ScriptBuiltIn.ARABIC);
    matches (on each repetition) one Unicode character in the ARABIC script.
